node.text:
As the saying goes, so little time, so much to do…buti nalang I’m able to cope with my busy schedule with the help of some pretty cool gadgets that make my life easier! Check out this IGTV and watch a day in my life with the HUAWEI Matepad 11 and my little helpers, the M-Pencil 2nd Gen and Freebuds 4! I love how integrated they are with each other (watch til end to see their amazing features!) so there’s more time for me to hang out, relax and just chill. ❤️
 
Visit the site below for more info!
 
https://bit.ly/PiaMatePad11
 
#HUAWEIMatePad11PH
#MadeByMatePad
@huaweimobilePH

node.text:
WE CAN STOP THIS. 🙏🏼 One of the main barriers that undermine access to prevention and treatment services is stigma and discrimination, which is still pervasive in healthcare settings, at home, at work and in society. Many people are not accessing services out of fear of being recognised or judged or out of personal safety and security. WE MUST CHANGE THIS.

These are trying times; we must not lose sight of the goals and ensure #HIV remains a key priority issue. Together we can, together we are stronger, together we can end #AIDS.

PLEASE SIGN the letter and join us in asking world leaders to fulfil their commitments to ending AIDS as a public health threat by 2030. Visit 👉🏼 www.unaids.org for more info.

@unaids_ap @unaidsglobal @loveyourself.ph

node.title: AIDS is not over, but it can be.

node.text:
I used to be a person that didn't put much thought into my nutrition and recovery. But all that changed this year. I've been more aware of  my health and what my body can do. And what I need to do to take care of it. I've learned how important it is to take care of our health. Aanhin mo naman ang ganda kung hindi mo naman inaalagaan ang health mo, diba? Especially this year, we don't want that.  
Every time I endorse a brand I always make sure it works, that I believe in it and that I use it in real life. That’s why before I accepted being 4Life Philippines brand ambassador I made  sure  I’ve used their  products first for a few months before partnering with them.   I'm really happy with the results and I feel great! @4lifephilippinesofficial is popularly known as the immune system company. They are based in the US and  have been manufacturing supplements for the past  22 years.   That is why I'm thrilled to announce my partnership as 4Life Philippines first brand ambassador. In the coming months, I'll be sharing more about their products like the Transfer Factor. It's backed up by research and I've also done my personal research about it. Really excited to share more about it with you.   Also, another thing I love about 4Life is their passion for helping children all over their world through their service pillar "Foundation 4Life". So for sure may mga gagawin rin kaming advocacy work together. :)

Learn more about 4Life Philippines, link in my bio✨

#TheImmuneSystemCompany
#ImmuneHealthAwareness
#DoLifeDiffrently
#QueenPiaX4Life
#QueenPiaIsHome4Life

node.text:
For the second episode of Holding Space, join us as we talk about eating, how we see our bodies and understanding Bulimia Nervosa through the help of one of our champions, Kyra. Madami tayong matutunan sa topic na ito. It is something na hindi natin masyado napaguusapan. ❤️🙏🏼

Here’s a little background on what this episode is about: Eating is one of the ways we share valuable moments with our loved ones and friends. Little did we know that some people experience some difficulty when it comes to eating and how their body responds differently to food intake. Some may even experience receiving comments about how they look and how they eat, and these contribute to how they see themselves and their bodies.

Premiering now! Check out the link in my stories to watch ❤️

Get ready to #GOforConservation and let’s be virtual running buddies! ❤️🏃🍃

@wwfphilippines is celebrating its 60th Anniversary with a virtual run to raise funds to support our conservation efforts across the country.

Registration is ongoing and will run until October 10. Virtual runners* who will successfully complete 20km, 40km, or 60km cumulative distance over the course of the run from October 1-31 will receive a WWF 60th Anniversary commemorative finishers’ kit.

For more details, download pinoy.fit/atleta NOW and REGISTER!

*We kindly ask our virtual runners to follow COVID-19 protocols when applicable. Please wear your masks, avoid crowds, and run alone if possible. Let's stay safe and healthy! Btw you can also use your treadmill or walking pad at home 🙏🏼❤️
